# CODEOWNERS — Documentation Ownership Map
#
# Maps documentation directories to the teams responsible for review.
# Update these paths and team handles to match your organization.
#
# Format: <path-pattern> <github-team-or-user>
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for all documentation not matched by a more specific rule
*   @docs-team

# API documentation by service — assign to the owning engineering team
docs/api/payments/          @payments-team
docs/api/fraud/             @fraud-team
docs/api/customers/         @customers-team
docs/api/notifications/     @notifications-team

# Governance files — documentation platform team must approve all changes
templates/                  @docs-platform
schema/                     @docs-platform
validation/                 @docs-platform
prompts/                    @docs-platform

# Operations and architecture
docs/operations/            @platform-infra
docs/architecture/          @architecture-team

# Security-sensitive documentation — requires security review
docs/authentication/        @security-team @docs-team
docs/authorization/         @security-team @docs-team
